## Render MCP Tools Available

When working with Render, use these MCP tools:

### List/View
- `mcp_render_list_services` - List all services
- `mcp_render_list_deploys` - List deploys for a service (requires serviceId)
- `mcp_render_list_logs` - List logs (requires resource ID)
- `mcp_render_list_postgres_instances` - List Postgres databases
- `mcp_render_list_key_value` - List Key Value stores
- `mcp_render_list_workspaces` - List workspaces

### Get Details
- `mcp_render_get_service` - Get service details (requires serviceId)
- `mcp_render_get_deploy` - Get deploy details (requires serviceId, deployId)
- `mcp_render_get_metrics` - Get performance metrics
- `mcp_render_get_postgres` - Get Postgres instance details
- `mcp_render_get_key_value` - Get Key Value instance details

### Create
- `mcp_render_create_web_service` - Create new web service
- `mcp_render_create_static_site` - Create new static site
- `mcp_render_create_postgres` - Create new Postgres database
- `mcp_render_create_key_value` - Create new Key Value store

### Update
- `mcp_render_update_web_service` - Update web service
- `mcp_render_update_static_site` - Update static site
- `mcp_render_update_environment_variables` - Update env vars

### Other
- `mcp_render_select_workspace` - Select workspace (ask user first!)
- `mcp_render_query_render_postgres` - Run read-only SQL queries

